                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d542">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">641.0031/67: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-25T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 25, 1936—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>283. Department’s 234, July 3, and your 349, July 16.<note n="41"
                        xml:id="d542fn41">Latter not printed.</note> The British Ambassador came to
                    see me on July 20 and handed me as a matter of courtesy an extract of Mr.
                    Runciman’s speech that you transmitted in your 349. In the light of this speech
                    believe it advisable that memorandum transmitted in Department’s 234 be not
                    presented until revised. Department will transmit revision.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
